  "texts": [
    "An eHealth system can be made fault-tolerant, dependable, and protected against DoS using a decentralized blockchain controller.",
    "Furthermore, current eHealth systems based on blockchain did not progress BCMs or privacyaware job handling techniques.",
    "To fill this gap, our proposed SSEHCET deploys blockchain at different tiers (as outlined in the proposed methodology section) to provide secure eHealth services.",
    "Related workThis section will explore existing studies that used cutting-edge technologies especially Blockchain, edge/fog computing, and Cloud to address eHealth security issues.In the article [11], the authors suggest a Blockchainenabled decentralized electronic healthcare architecture that is composed of three layers: 1) The Sensing layer, which consists of several medical sensors that are often placed on or inside a patient's body and transfer data to a smartphone.",
    "2) The Edge Networks are made up of devices that are close to the data-detecting IoT devices."
  ],
